      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ES POR AMOR (3) was first up from a spell last start and saluted by 5 lengths at this track over 1200m. Has a terrific record here with three wins and two placings from five starts. Leading contender. COSMIC STRIPES (1) did a great job to score by a nose over today's course and distance when resuming from a layoff last time out. Nicely placed to score once again. TODO CAMBIA (12) is a talented colt who tackled a tougher race at his last run on October 4 and finished tenth behind Real Rim over 2000m in the Group 1 Jockey Club at this track. Has the gate speed to take up a forward position. Should be involved in the finish. MUCHACHO CALAVERA (5) is close to a win after a string of minor placings, the latest when second over 1200m at this track. Suitably placed so anticipating another big run.",
